Amendment No. 2 to HB0005
Terry
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 419 House Bill No. 5*
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 29-39-102(d), is amended by adding
the following as a new subdivision:
(5)
(A) Wrongful death of an unborn child at any stage of gestation in utero
when an abortion-inducing drug is sent directly to a patient by a defendant via
courier, delivery, or mail service in violation of § 63-6-1103(b).
(B) For purposes of this subdivision (d)(5), "abortion-inducing drug"
means mifepristone or misoprostol. This subdivision (d)(5) does not prohibit the
lawful use of mifepristone or misoprostol by a pharmacist or physician.
(C) This subdivision (d)(5) does not apply to:
(i) A pharmacist;
(ii) A physician;
(iii) A motor carrier or freight forwarder, as defined in 49 U.S.C. §
13102; or
(iv) An air carrier, as defined in 49 U.S.C. § 40102.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect July 1, 2026, the public welfare requiring it, and
applies to a cause of action filed on or after that date.
